8353, "Commandant Sorenson ? Lloyd ! Mon Dieu, non. À tous les pilotes, nous avons perdu l'Indus, on abandonne la mission !"

8354, "Ici le Commandant Kyrematen. Mon vaisseau est en difficulté. Je sais que vous pouvez faire mieux que ça, Dieux de la Guerre."

8355, "Indus, on ne va pas y arriver. Lloyd, je... - *parasites*"

8356, "Je détecte une défaillance catastrophique des systèmes à bord du Yangzi... aucun survivant. Sortez d'ici, dieux de la guerre. La mission est un fiasco."

8357, "Escadrille Taureau écrasée. 4 Nyx de moins à s'inquiéter."

8358, "Escadrille Balance descendue. Ça devrait perturber le réseau de combat tev."

8359, "Bien joué, pilotes, la Sirène est muselée. Nous poursuivons l'engagement prévu."

8360, "Et... c'est tout pour l'escorte ! Bravo zulu, Dieux de la Guerre, on vient de nettoyer la maison avec une unité tactique de première ligne."

8361, "Devrions-nous prendre un moment pour rendre hommage aux morts de l'ennemi ? Qu'en pensez-vous, pilotes ?"

8362, "Je pense que nous avons déjà passé beaucoup de temps à les respecter, Yangzi."

8363, "Oui, nous nous sommes vraiment engagés dans une communication intense avec eux. J'ai eu un dialogue profond avec l'un d'eux, vraiment."

8364, "Tirez quelques coups dans les collecteurs des moteurs de l'Agincourt, pilotes. Si ce vaisseau saute, nous avons manqué notre chance."

8365, "<intercepté> Agincourt, Sirène. La situation se dégrade. Envoyez une nacelle ou un chasseur au plus vite. Nous tiendrons aussi longtemps que nous le pouvons."

8366, "La corvette Sirène a été détruite.  Que son équipage trouve la paix."

8367, "Bon sang, vous avez vu ça ? C'était un très joli boom."

8368, "Très bien, je pense que nous avons assez pilonné l'Agincourt. Artilleurs, marquez l'Agincourt comme cible interdite de tir jusqu'à ce que vous receviez un contrordre. Faites passer le mot à Tactique du Yangzi, s'il vous plaît."

8369, "GTL Agincourt, vos escortes ont été détruites et vos moteurs sont en arrêt de sécurité. Rendez-vous, ou nous vous envoyons dans l'espace."

8370, "Ici le Commandant Sibrine. Afin de préserver la vie de mon équipage, et conformément à l'Ordre Général 18, je remets par la présente mon vaisseau aux mains de la Fédération Terrienne Unie."

8371, "Agincourt, je détecte de l'activité dans vos baies logistiques. Soyez avertis que si vous tentez de détruire vos propres fournitures ou équipements, nos marines vous tueront vous et votre équipage."

8372, "Et nous ne voulons vraiment pas faire ça, Commandant Sibrine. Les crimes de guerre perturbent vraiment mon calme intérieur, vous voyez ce que je veux dire ? C'est une sérieuse merde zen que vous mettez en danger ici."

8373, "Très bien. Pour information, je tiens à ce que l'on sache que ma décision d'abandonner les protocoles de destruction de la cargaison a été prise dans le but de préserver mon équipage."

8374, "Ça, c'est du dévouement, Sibrine. Ne vous inquiétez pas, vous pourrez passer le reste de la guerre à 'préserver' votre équipage dans un camp de Solis Lacus."

8375, "Nous signalons la Gloire avec des coordonnées précises. Les Marines seront sur place dans moins d'une minute."

8376, "C'est la Gloire. Nous allons pénétrer dans l'Agincourt. Équipes de feu Alpha et Bravo, tenez-vous prêts à entrer. Vérifiez vos armures, tout le monde."

8377, "Soyez prudent, Gloire. Rappelez-vous ce qui est arrivé au Juniper pendant l'abordage du Kubara. Gardez vos cloisons de sécurité prêtes au cas où quelqu'un lancerait une bombe nucléaire de poche."

8378, "(fr)No need to mother-hen us, Captain Kyrematen. We've got it. Alpha, Bravo, ROE is weapons tight. Any negligent discharge with that 15 mil and you could hole something critical."

8379, "(fr)Good job handling that snag, Wargods. We're in position. Agincourt airlock is handshaking and opening. Cobra drones, go...in and clear, thermal clear, GTDS clear...okay, entrance is clear. Go go go."

8380, "(fr)-eft clear! Alpha Six, we're in, following the Cobras. Check your corners, people! Watch that companionway, Sev!"

8381, "(fr)Bravo Six moving towards the CIC. No sign of resistance. Check and move, people! I want Cobras under that hatch and a wall flood on the compartment!"

8382, "(fr)Gloire, Alpha Six. We have the Agincourt's Marine detachment in peaceful custody. We've secured their magazines and the armory, including some intact Komodo suits."

8383, "(fr)All right, Marines, we're putting the capture team aboard. Secure CIC, damage control, nav, and engineering."

8384, "(fr)Registering meson reactor containment failure aboard the Elissa. Scratch one Hyperion."

8385, "(fr)Catastrophic hull failure in progress aboard the Utica. Scratch target."

8386, "(fr)The Agincourt has been destroyed! How the hell did we manage that, people? Let's get out of here before more Tevs arrive!"

8387, "(fr)Simms, I'm in trouble here!"

8388, "(fr)Copy that, Laporte. Hold it together a little longer, rook, and I'll see what I can do."

8389, "(fr)I got you, Two. Stay defensive, break if you get spiked, and keep a thumb on the CM ejector toggle."

8390, "(fr)You're a regular duckling, Laporte. Stand by, I'm inbound."

8391, "(fr)Damsel in distress! I'm inbound, stand by."

8392, "(fr)Whoa, uh-oh. Uh, Simms, I'm in trouble here!"

8393, "(fr)Simms, the Tevs are giving me some real grief."

8394, "(fr)One, Two. I'm in a tight spot. Could use some cover here!"

8395, "(fr)Oy, bugger me! We've got an arseload of bombers jumping in! Think our op's been tumbled?"

8396, "(fr)No, they're just dropping back in from a raid, hoping to top off fuel and bombs at the Agincourt. Splash 'em quick, wargods."

8397, "(fr)Keep your PDS at the ready, Gloire. There's a lot of them and we're liable to let a few leak."

8398, "(fr)We lost the Gloire and the boarding party! Op's a wash, people. Let's get our people off the Agincourt, blow the ship, and get out."

8399, "(fr)Tev fire has saturated our point defenses and passed our safe armor threshold. We're on the red-line now pilots."

8400, "(fr)So much for the bombers. Almost feel sorry for the poor bastards, don't you? A third the training their fighter pilots get, glorified warhead buses to fly without even a turret to give 'em cover, and half the time their escorts get pulled."

8401, "(fr)If their bombers are such pilot-killers, why do they keep the stupid things around? "

8402, "(fr)Operational surplus, I guess. Just like the Myrmidon. The fact is that for every unescorted flight we catch like that, three more get through to blitz some unguarded station or harry a warship."

8403, "(fr)Ay, Indus. Did those pilots get a transmission off?"

8404, "(fr)The Boanerges strike transmitted six distress calls, but they couldn't overpower our jamming."

8405, "(fr)Jump flash! I've got two GTVA wings, a cruiser, and an AWACS inbound! They must be here to resupply!"

8406, "(fr)Pilots, scramble to destroy that AWACS! She's isolating our jamming frequencies and in less than four minutes she'll broadcast our position straight to Admiral Steele!"

8407, "(fr)Play it safe, people. Watch the Aeolus, and remember, no survivors. If anyone jumps home, we're racked."

8408, "(fr)Pilots, the Panopticon just punched a transmission through our jamming. Recon reports that the Atrée and a hunter-killer corvette group are coming down on us. We need to get out, now."

8409, "(fr)The AWACS is offline and breaking apart. Operational security preserved. Mop up any remaining fighters - if you keep them in ACM they're not likely to risk jumping."

8410, "(fr)Good work, everyone. That was well handled, and those Tevs gave us a good fight. I'm officially proud of you all."

8411, "(fr)We've got some bad news, pilots. The Agincourt's subspace drive was either damaged during the attack or sabotaged during the boarding. Without a new motivator, this ship is going nowhere."

8412, "(fr)Request mission update, Indus. If we can't jump the Agincourt out by its next scheduled check-in, we're going to be overwhelmed by Tev reinforcements."

8413, "(fr)Negative, pilots. We have a contingency for this event. There's a local gate to Mars less than six days' sublight travel from here. We'll conduct repairs with onboard supplies and bring the Agincourt out on fusion drives."

8414, "(fr)Eish, six days without Jump Fives or raids? Did we finally stumble on the secret formula to earn some leave in Two Fleet?"

8415, "(fr)That's exactly right, Olefumi. They give you a week for every logistics ship you bring in and a bonus week for the Atrée. Hit the deck, pilots! I won't rest easy until we've got this sucker locked down in Mars orbit, so let's get moving!"

8416, "(fr)Acknowledged. Standing by for Indus autoland handshake."

8417, "(fr)The Agincourt is preparing to jump. Destroy that engine subsystem, pilots, or our target is going to slip away."

8418, "(fr)What do you think, Captain Simms? We're doing all right so far. I think we might just pull this off."

8419, "(fr)How very earnest of you, Laporte...but yeah, assuming a hunter-killer group doesn't pop in to rearm and rearmor, this might not be a bloodbath. And that's as optimistic as I'll get, so don't push it!"

8420, "(fr)Come on, wargods, splash that AWACS! We didn't come this far just to get tumbled now!"

8421, "(fr)We're reading a subspace exit. The mission is compromised. What the hell happened, people? Let's get out of here before hunter-killers arrive - we have some explaining to do!"

8422, "(fr)Indus control, the Agincourt is ours. Repeat, we have control of the Agincourt."

8423, "(fr)Someone on the Agincourt is making trouble. I'm picking up activity in the launch bay...heads up! Enemy fighters!"

8424, "(fr)They're just a distraction. The other hangar bay is launching escape pods. They're going to jump clear and signal for help."

8425, "(fr)Laporte, take out the pods! Wargods, splash those fighters and give her some room to work!"

8426, "(fr)Yes, sir! Massacring escape pods!"

8427, "(fr)All pods splashed. I hope those things were unmanned, not full of panicked deckhands."

8428, "(fr)Clean kills on all three bandits. Slippery little creatures."

8429, "(fr)Warbird ejecting!"

8430, "(fr)I'm hit! I'm going down!"

8431, "(fr)Oh, bugger me!"

8432, "(fr)I heard they gave us leave for good looks."

8433, "(fr)With Olefumi around, it's no wonder the Yangzi never gets a break."

8434, "(fr)Next time Ogre's got a Tev on his six I think I'll just let things take their course. It's better for all of us."

8435, "(fr)Jealousy is such an ugly emotion."

