8776, "(fr)Holy - Indus control, I'm getting red lights on my board. Long-range communications are down!"

8777, "(fr)Captain Sorensen, we don't have time for this posturing! The clock's ticking on the Pesedjet's reactor failure!"

8778, "(fr)Captain Price, we're picking up massive jamming from your corvette. What is the meaning of this?"

8779, "(fr)A little insurance policy, Captain Sorensen. You want to do things your way, fine. Help out the Vasudans, but no reinforcements."

8780, "(fr)GTT Sampson, on approach to dock with Pesedjet's ventral airlock. Federation forces, if you are armed, hold your fire."

8781, "(fr)In which case, Captain, I'm sure you won't object to us returning the favour. Comms, hit them with a wide-frequency blast. Jam their long-ranged communications."

8782, "(fr)This is Medic Team Alpha! We're experiencing massive internal detonations! The Vasudan engineers we're patching up say that internal safeties have failed!"

8783, "(fr)Damn! We're scrambling repair equipment from the Indus, but it's going to be several minutes before we can load a shuttle. Do the best you can with what you have."

8784, "(fr)We've got repair technicians with heavy field equipment on board the Sampson. Standard procedure for answering a stricken vessel. You could learn from our example next time."

8785, "(fr)And your transport carries only the barest medical facilities, Captain. If your engineers save the ship, we'll save the crew. Once the Pesedjet is out of danger...we'll work from there."

8786, "(fr)Touche, Captain Sorensen."

8787, "(fr)Touche, Captain Sorensen. Here's my proposal. We stand down, and you do the same. We pool our resources, repair this Vasudan ship, and then we go our separate ways."

8788, "(fr)The Vasudans continue to help us supply, while you gain favour with Khonsu for when you negotiate the terms of your surrender."

8789, "(fr)Indus, I'm reading a global weapons power down on the Arethusa and Tev fighters. They've disengaged and are pulling back."

8790, "(fr)What extraordinary times we live in. Very well, Captain Price. The welfare of the Pesedjet will take precedence for now. However, if you do anything to compromise the ceasefire, we will not hesitate to open fire."

8791, "(fr)Red and black ants, building bowling alleys together from caterpillar teeth."

8792, "(fr)This is doing my head in. Sitting this close to Tevs without shots firing."

8793, "(fr)Normally I'd be itching to open fire, but...do you think this is how it was supposed to be? That maybe this is the first sane thing that's happened since the Tevs showed up?"

8794, "(fr)This is Medic Team Alpha. Engineer crisis teams have managed to seal off compromised areas. Radiation levels are falling, and we've managed to secure most of the surviving crew. Good thing those techs came when they did."

8795, "(fr)Ever the romantic, Laporte. Frankly, this is absurd. Sooner or later we'll be shooting at each other again. Let's just get it over with."

8796, "(fr)If you ask me, a little danger brings a certain buzz to first meetings. Has anyone ever told you how lovely you sound on the comm?"

8797, "(fr)Lieutenant Fabian Kurniadi. at your service. 181st Bloodhounds squadron, GTD Carthage. Callsign 'Anansi'...goodness knows why."

8798, "(fr)Captain Lorna Simms, Indus Wargods. Now you'll know who I am when our little hugbox breaks up and I kill you."

8799, "(fr)Only one side can win. Choose."

8800, "(fr)..."

8801, "(fr)It is the way of things. You must choose."

8802, "(fr)Sublieutenant Noemi Laporte, Indus Wargods. Have a care with Captain Simms, Tev. You don't want her on the wrong side of the IFF spectrum."

8803, "(fr)So I've heard. Your squadron has Admiral Steele's attention, Sublieutenant Laporte. You lot seem determined to win this war all by yourself."

8804, "(fr)It's always good to verify our strategic impact from a human source, Lieutenant Kurniadi. How about some hard numbers? What's the bounty on my head? "

8805, "(fr)Big enough to make me take notice, and my father's a shipping magnate. The catch is, of course, that no one survives to collect...or I'm sure I would have heard reports of your charms."

8806, "(fr)This is a bad line of work for an amateur Casanova, Lieutenant. When you get shot down out here, it's dangerously literal."

8807, "(fr)Medic Team Alpha here. Preliminary triage has been completed. We're moving the critically wounded onto the Littman for emergency care. I wish to state for the record that the conduct of GTVA engineering teams has been more than exemplary."

8808, "(fr)Acknowledged, MT Alpha. Good work. Well, Captain Price, it seems thanks are in order."

8809, "(fr)Eyes up pilots, new contact! It's the heavy frigate Hesperia!"

8810, "(fr)Priority message to Captain Aldred. Tell him to cease fire immediately, the Arethusa is a non-combatant!"

8811, "(fr)Scorpio wing and the Arethusa have gone weapons hot!"

8812, "(fr)Littman, you are to disengage from the Pesedjet. We're pulling you out of the battlezone."

8813, "(fr)Commencing undocking process now. Be advised, we've got Vasudan wounded on board. Captain Apries has demanded that we return them before we undock."

8814, "(fr)There's no time, Littman. Get out of there now, before the Tevs make you a target!"

8815, "(fr)Pilots, evasive manoeuvres! Watch the fire, it's close quarters at the moment!"

8816, "(fr)The Arethusa has opened fire!"

8817, "(fr)So much for a ceasefire. All batteries, return fire. Fighters, form a defensive screen!"

8818, "(fr)The Littman has made it out. Pilots, follow us back to Mars on the double!"

8819, "(fr)Oh, damn it...Tev fighters on an attack run! The Arethusa has opened fire!"

8820, "(fr)We surrender, you traitorous sons of bitches! Hold your fire!"

8821, "(fr)Hesperia, this is the Indus. The Arethusa was assisting our humanitarian mission for the Pesedjet. You've just destroyed a non-combatant under a ceasefire."

8822, "(fr)Ceasefire? Pardon me, Captain Sorensen, but I got no notice from Command that such a ceasefire was in place. Admiral Calder deployed us to secure the area after we lost contact with you. The Arethusa was a hostile target, and by definition a combatant."

8823, "(fr)Seems like the status quo has returned to this little area of space, Laporte. How do you fancy the outcome of this 'humanise the enemy' experiment?"

8824, "(fr)I can't complain, One. We're still alive. But I can't help but wonder what would have happened if it had lasted a little longer..."

8825, "(fr)Still, I guess best intentions aren't enough to stop the fighting. It's too late for that. This war won't end until one side wins...and I'd rather it be us."

8826, "(fr)Laporte, we'll make a Martian of you yet."

8827, "(fr)Pilots, this mission is over. Bring yourselves in. Gamma wing from the Hesperia will take over escort duty."

