8978, "(fr)It's beautiful...my god, Laporte, look at the Earth, off to the left. It looks so fragile. And the city here, in the desolation. Reminds me of home..."

8979, "(fr)Wow, boss, I'm thunderstruck. You're dangerously close to expressing an emotion other than casual rage."

8980, "(fr)I miss Mars. I miss looking out at the rust desert and the dome lights, feeling proud of what we'd built...what Ubuntu built. We really had something special here, didn't we?"

8981, "(fr)The human spirit, finally unchained. That was what Elder Mandho used to tell me. Dad said it was a nicely paced socioeconomic boom. My mom just called it paradise."

8982, "(fr)A place where every last human had the drive and the ability to work to her full potential. And once we had that, we'd go back to the stars, and nothing would stop us."

8983, "(fr)Luna City's an economic hub. Most of the people here are financeers and traders...the creditors and stockbrokers who run the free market economy."

8984, "(fr)And then the Tevs kicked down the door and blew it all away."

8985, "(fr)They're not monsters, Captain. Just people like us...only they didn't get a sealed system full of riches. They had to go out there and face down the demons. I kill them, but I don't know if I hate them."

8986, "(fr)I think they lost something out there, and we have to -"

8987, "(fr)How can you not hate them? We've seen thousands die at their hands. Name a single good thing that's come from this atrocity!"

8988, "(fr)Remember when we were staying at Karen's place on Mars? And you started yelling at Levi in your sleep, and then fell out of your bunk?"

8989, "(fr)Alpha wing, Knights. Elder Taudigani is aboard the shuttle, and final flight preparations are complete. We're reading a lot of comm traffic between your fighters - is there a problem?"

